MinStack:
`pop()`
`popMin()`: pop (i.e. remove) the minimum integer within the stack
`push()`: return false if an integer is already present in the stack, return true if integer did not exist previously and push the integer on top of the stack.

Answer:
I did this in Java, so used a Custom Doubly Linked List and a TreeMap

The `DLL` had a head and tail, elements were inserted removed from it.
The `TreeMap` maintained the <Key : value, Value: Reference to the item in DLL>

The DLL helps us maintain the stack order.
The Map helps us get the minimum in a cheaper way.

Please let me know if the solution could be any better.

```
class Solution {

    static Node head, tail;
    static TreeMap<Integer, Node> map;

    public Solution () {
        head = new Node();
        tail = new Node();
        head.next = tail;
        tail.prev = head;
        map = new TreeMap<>();
    }

    public static boolean push(int value) {
        if (map.containsKey(value)) {
            return false;
        }

        Node newNode = new Node(value);
        newNode.prev = tail.prev;
        newNode.prev.next = newNode;
        newNode.next = tail;
        tail.prev = newNode;
        map.put(value, newNode);
        return true;
    }

    public static int popMin() throws Exception {
        if (map.size() == 0) throw new Exception("no items in stack");
        int min = map.firstKey();
        Node minNode = map.get(min);
        minNode.prev.next = minNode.next;
        minNode.next.prev = minNode.prev;
        map.remove(min);
        minNode = null;
        return min;
    }

    public static int pop() throws Exception {
        if (map.size() == 0) throw new Exception("no items in stack");
        Node popNode = head.next;
        int item = popNode.val;
        head.next = popNode.next;
        popNode.next.prev = head;
        map.remove(item);
        popNode = null;
        return item;

    }
}

class Node {
        int val;
        Node next;
        Node prev;

        public Node() {
        }

        public Node(int val) {
            this.val = val;
            this.next = null;
            this.prev = null;
         }
}

